detail:
            This is a great opportunity to join a rapidly expanding practice within the leading company in the global forensic field.
You will be using your strong analytical skills will be harnessed in order to provide high-impact solutions to pressing business needs for some of the biggest clients in this space. You will be scoping and leading the delivery of analytical work with the help of a team under your guidance.
Requirements:
Experience of leading and managing project-based work;
Significant experience in at least one of the following technical areas:
Data analysis and modelling using standard tools (e.g. SAS, R, Matlab, Scala);
Data analysis and modelling using network analysis and graph analytics software (e.g. i2, Neo4j);
Strong scripting or programming skills (e.g. C#, VB.net, Java, Python);
Statistical / predictive modelling techniques and machine learning algorithms (e.g. regression, clustering, decision trees);
 Forensic Technology experience is NOT necessary however experience of working in or working on projects in regulated industries, particularly financial services will help your case.
